KeyboardEvent - Class in org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.event
The KeyboardEvent class stores information about a keyboard event
KeyboardEvent(char, int) - Constructor for class org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.event.KeyboardEvent
This constructor takes the event's key's character and key code and creates an Event
KeyboardInput - Class in org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input
The KeyboardInput class that contains all of the key codes for the keyboard used by MyEngine when calling events and also holds boolean values for each key that can be statically accessed which are equal to true when that key is currently pressed (Down).
KeyboardInput() - Constructor for class org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.KeyboardInput
 
keyChar - Variable in class org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.event.KeyboardEvent
This character is the character of the key associated with this KeyboardEvent
keyCode - Variable in class org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.event.KeyboardEvent
This integer is the key code of the key associated with this KeyboardEvent in MyEngine format (Represented in KeyboardInput)
keyPressed(KeyEvent) - Method in class org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.InputManagerJava
This method is called when a key pressed event has occurred
keyReleased(KeyEvent) - Method in class org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.InputManagerJava
This method is called when a key released event has occurred
keyTyped(KeyEvent) - Method in class org.simplecorporation.myengine.core.input.InputManagerJava
This method is called when a key typed event has occurred
